{
  "texts": [
    "While some research suggests the possibility that NPI fatigue may make it unlikely for noncompliant individuals to readopt compliant behavior [21], other work suggests that well-implemented public advocacy programs can increase compliance with NPIs [31,50].",
    "Accordingly, for full generality, we allow noncompliant individuals to become compliant again with transfer rate ν ≥ 0.",
    "We note that this effect can be removed by setting ν = 0 if one prefers and all subsequent derivations and theorems still hold.Finally, we assume that any newly added members of the population are noncompliant with probability ξ ∈ [0, 1].",
    "Defining the actively mixing infectious population by I (M) = (1 -α)I + I * and the total noncompliant population N * = S * + I * + R *.",
    "All of these modeling decisions lead to the equationsdS dt = (1 -ξ)b -β(1 -α)SI (M) -µSN * + νS * -δS, dI dt = β(1 -α)SI (M) -γI -µIN * + νI * -δI, dR dt = γI -µRN * + νR * -δR, dS * dt = ξb -βS * I (M) + µSN * -νS * -δS *, dI * dt = βS * I (M) -γI * + µIN * -νI * -δI *, dR * dt = γI * + µRN * -νR * -δR *."
  ]
}